comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T20:56:30.024Z",codex-agent,"Audit evidence 2026-07-04 continuation: inspected all statuses with pm list --status all, pm stats, pm aggregate, pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift, pm health --check-only --summary, pm next, active duplicate-title scan, active parent-link scan, and live gh issue/pr list. Live totals: 1506 pm items, 1514 history streams, 24446 history entries. Status distribution: 37 open, 13 in_progress, 1444 closed, 12 canceled, 0 blocked. Type distribution: 1 Milestone, 81 Epics, 286 Features, 286 Issues, 524 Tasks, 224 Chores, 17 Plans, 50 Decisions, 36 Stories, 1 Reminder. Active structure: 50 active items, zero active non-epic orphans, zero duplicate-looking active titles, pm next ready=36 blocked=0. GitHub cross-check: one open issue GH-427, already tracked by in_progress pm-lt6n; zero open PRs. Existing broad audit lineages pm-y904 and pm-osea are closed with evidence and remain canonical, so no duplicate audit item was created. Residual governance: validate reports validate_resolution_missing_fields:268 on closed historical items, already represented by open pm-e9zh; active metadata filter only flags claimed epic pm-4ak1 for missing estimate/reviewer/sprint/release metadata, noted there without taking over the claim."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T10:24:45.228Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-06-07 ecosystem audit (plan pm-8u2a): rebuilt the empty forward backlog — 71 new OPEN items across all 9 capability epics + 2 new ADRs (pm-7sq6 coverage governance, pm-cc04 agent self-repair). Delivered by 5 specialized audit sub-agents (disjoint epic scopes). pm context now returns actionable leaf work again."
body: "## Vision\npm is a universal, agent-optimized, git-native project management CLI that ships PM primitives via an SDK so any project can fully customize and optimize it. Guiding principle: **project management = context management** — an agent must be able to rebuild full working context from the pm CLI alone.\n\nThis milestone groups the post-v0.1 capability epics and their open backlog (surfaced by the 2026-05-31 ecosystem audit pm-w7f2; last reconciled by audit #4 pm-osea on 2026-07-04). PRD post-v0.1 roadmap items (advanced search tuning, adapter optimization, sandbox API surface) live under the relevant capability epic as concrete, dedup-checked work.\n\n## Living capability epics (index)\nEach is a permanently-open living backlog; new work in that area lands there. Scope In/Out boundaries are stated in each epic charter so no two overlap.\n\n- pm-mpbb — CLI command surface & agent ergonomics\n- pm-o2kc — Storage, history & data durability\n- pm-ydp6 — Search & semantic retrieval\n- pm-ugqx — Extension & package platform maturity (incl. SDK, plugins)\n- pm-33cw — Governance, validation & data quality\n- pm-dj98 — Concurrency & multi-agent safety\n- pm-5oj5 — Observability, telemetry & health\n- pm-8jdc — Schema, config & universal customization (incl. profiles)\n- pm-5k4v — MCP server & contract platform\n- pm-92if — CodeFactor / source-code quality (A→A+)\n- pm-u9d0 — Docs, onboarding, release & CI\n- pm-m2u1 — Architecture Decision Records (living decision log)\n\n## Convention\nCapability epics stay OPEN even with zero open children (living backlogs). Audits are CREATE-ONLY on closed items (changelog buckets by updated_at). Every pm validate/health warning maps to exactly one open remediation item."
